22/11/2006
LONDON, Great Britain -- Turkey's EU integration prospects were the focus of talks between Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and his British counterpart Tony Blair in London on Tuesday (November 21st). Both reaffirmed their countries' support for Turkey's EU membership as important for the Union and for regional stability. They also agreed that the usual conditions and terms must be applied in Turkey's case. 
In other news Tuesday, the new head of the European Commission Delegation to Ankara, Ambassador Marc Pierini, formally presented his credentials to Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer. The French diplomat succeeds Germany's Hansjoerg Kretschmer, whose term expired earlier this month. (Naftemporiki - 22/11/06; ANA-MPA, ERT, ANKA, Zaman - 21/11/06)
